================================================================================================
== Welcome to the Automatic Telescope Control System: Stargazer
================================================================================================

This repository is for the Ruby on Rails web application which allows users to remotely schedule telescope positions.

For more information about the Stargazer project, please visit our wiki page at:
http://wiki.github.com/RedTeamCOSC470/Stargazer/

================================================================================================
== Repositories:
================================================================================================

-- Web Application:
Desc: Handles the client requests from PC and mobile device users.
Link: http://github.com/RedTeamCOSC470/Stargazer

-- Telescope-Controlling Application:
Desc: Handles actual telescope positioning and signalling of the camera to capture images.
Link: http://github.com/RedTeamCOSC470/Controller-Application

-- Documentation:
Desc: Stores all documentation and design related to the Stargazer project.
Link: http://github.com/RedTeamCOSC470/Documentation

================================================================================================
== Gems Used:
================================================================================================

# for creating initial CSS/views:
web-app-theme
http://github.com/pilu/web-app-theme

# for authentication/login subsystem:
authlogic
http://github.com/binarylogic/authlogic

# for time validation:
validates_timeliness
http://github.com/adzap/validates_timeliness
http://www.railslodge.com/plugins/1160-validates-timeliness

# for automatically creating some diagrams from Rails applications:
railroad

# for creating class diagrams:
yumlcmd
http://github.com/atog/yumlcmd

# for adding text field inputs for date/time:
chronic_duration

# for adding binary images to a model:
paperclip
http://github.com/thoughtbot/paperclip

# astronomy picture of the day - only for testing data:
dougsko-apod

# for separate CSS/views for mobile devices:
mobile-fu
http://github.com/brendanlim/mobile-fu
http://github.com/billymeltdown/mobile-fu

# for pagination:
will_paginate
http://wiki.github.com/mislav/will_paginate

# for calling Oracle PL/SQL procedures:
ruby-plsql
http://github.com/rsim/ruby-plsql
http://forums.oracle.com/forums/thread.jspa?threadID=555102 

# Oracle enhanced adapter for ActiveRecord:
oracle-enhanced
http://github.com/rsim/oracle-enhanced
http://ruby-oci8.rubyforge.org/en/

# for fast and easy deployment of Rails applications on Apache:
passenger
http://www.modrails.com/install.html

# for annotation of models (will comment in table column information):
annotate
http://pragdave.pragprog.com/pragdave/2006/02/annotate_models.html

# for auto completion in forms:
http://github.com/rails/auto_complete/

# calendar for selecting dates:
calendar_date_select
http://code.google.com/p/calendardateselect/
http://electronicholas.com/calendar